<paragraph blockId="5.[140,1095,160,1181]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991">
<emphasis box="[179,298,675,699]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991">Etymology</emphasis>
. This species was named after Professor Mike Cawthorn, University of Buckingham, Clore Laboratory, Buckingham MK18 1PQ, 
<collectingCountry box="[865,909,707,730]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991">UK</collectingCountry>
, for his help in water mite research.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[140,1095,160,1181]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991">
<emphasis box="[179,277,771,795]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991">Remarks</emphasis>
. A male, 
<specimenCount box="[390,512,771,795]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
and three nymphs were in the collection examined. The nymphs are ascribed to the new species based on the pedipalp having a small, but clearly developed, PII ventral projection. The positions of ventral glands, however, diVer to those adults where seta V3 is fused to L3 and the separate V3 gland lies anterior to E4 behind EpIV. In nymphs the V3 gland and seta are fused with L3 and located well posterior of E4. A similar chaetotaxy is apparent in adults of 
<taxonomicName box="[140,374,964,988]" class="Arachnida" family="Pontarachnidae" genus="Litarachna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="demhami">
<emphasis box="[140,374,964,988]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991">Litarachna demhami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These observations are not consistent with 
<bibRefCitation author="COOK, D. R." box="[925,1095,964,988]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991" pagination="259 - 264" refId="ref3807" refString="COOK, D. R., 1986, A freshwater species of Pontarachna, (Acari, Pontarachnidae) from South Africa, with a discussion of genital acetabula in the family, Annals of the Institute of the Biology, University Nac. Auton Mexico, 67 (2), 259 - 264." type="journal article" year="1986">Cook’s (1986)</bibRefCitation>
genital platelet hypothesis (see Discussion below). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wiles &amp; Chatterjee &amp; Troch" authorityYear="2002" box="[776,928,996,1020]" class="Arachnida" family="Pontarachnidae" genus="Litarachna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cawthorni">
<emphasis box="[776,928,996,1020]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991">L. cawthorni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Viets, 1984" authorityName="Viets" authorityYear="1984" box="[255,548,1028,1052]" class="Arachnida" family="Pontarachnidae" genus="Litarachna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabangensis">
<emphasis box="[255,416,1028,1052]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991">L. sabangensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="VIETS, K. O." box="[424,548,1028,1052]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991" pagination="350 - 352" refId="ref4113" refString="VIETS, K. O., 1984, A new species of Litarachna (Pontarachnidae, Hydrachnellae, Acari) from the coast of the Philippines, Zoologischer Anzeiger, 212, 350 - 352." type="journal article" year="1984">Viets, 1984</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="VIETS, K. O." box="[566,690,1028,1052]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991" pagination="350 - 352" refId="ref4113" refString="VIETS, K. O., 1984, A new species of Litarachna (Pontarachnidae, Hydrachnellae, Acari) from the coast of the Philippines, Zoologischer Anzeiger, 212, 350 - 352." type="journal article" year="1984">Viets, 1984</bibRefCitation>
) from the 
<collectingCountry box="[813,938,1028,1052]" name="Philippines" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991">Philippines</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Uchida, 1935" authorityName="Uchida" authorityYear="1935" class="Arachnida" family="Pontarachnidae" genus="Litarachna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kamui">
<emphasis box="[995,1094,1028,1052]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991">L. kamui</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="UCHIDA, T." box="[140,292,1061,1085]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991" pagination="183 - 196" refId="ref4006" refString="UCHIDA, T., 1935, Marine watermites from Japan, Journal of the Faculty of Sciences, Hokkaido University, Series VI Zoology, 4, 183 - 196." type="journal article" year="1935">Uchida, 1935</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[366,434,1061,1084]" name="Japan" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="UCHIDA, T." box="[455,607,1061,1085]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991" pagination="183 - 196" refId="ref4006" refString="UCHIDA, T., 1935, Marine watermites from Japan, Journal of the Faculty of Sciences, Hokkaido University, Series VI Zoology, 4, 183 - 196." type="journal article" year="1935">Uchida, 1935</bibRefCitation>
), both of which have a ventral projection to PII. The greatly indented posterior margin of EpIV of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wiles &amp; Chatterjee &amp; Troch" authorityYear="2002" box="[794,935,1093,1117]" class="Arachnida" family="Pontarachnidae" genus="Litarachna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cawthorni">
<emphasis box="[794,935,1093,1117]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991">L. cawthorni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clearly diVers from the straight posterior margin of EpIV in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viets" authorityYear="1984" box="[708,874,1125,1149]" class="Arachnida" family="Pontarachnidae" genus="Litarachna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabangensis">
<emphasis box="[708,874,1125,1149]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991">L. sabangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the large PII ventral projection contrasts to the small projection of 
<taxonomicName box="[764,866,1157,1181]" class="Arachnida" family="Pontarachnidae" genus="Litarachna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kaumi">
<emphasis box="[764,866,1157,1181]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1991">L. kaumi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
